description:
File: rust/lichen-gateway/src/bin/lichend.rs
Line: 266

When shutting down, the main loop aborts the sim_task immediately without draining pending transmissions. This could leave packets in the tx_send channel that never get transmitted.

Current code:
```rust
loop {
    tokio::select! {
        // ... branches ...
        _ = signal::ctrl_c() => {
            info!("shutting down");
            break;
        }
    }
}

sim_task.abort();  // Immediate abort, no graceful shutdown
```

Impact: On shutdown, pending outbound packets are lost. This is likely acceptable for a daemon shutdown, but could cause issues if the application expects reliable delivery.

Consider: For graceful shutdown, close the tx_send channel and wait for sim_task to finish transmitting, with a timeout:
```rust
_ = signal::ctrl_c() => {
    info!("shutting down");
    drop(tx_send);  // Signal sim_task to finish
    break;
}
// ...
// After the loop:
tokio::select! {
    _ = sim_task => {}
    _ = tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(5)) => {
        warn!("sim_task did not finish in time, aborting");
        sim_task.abort();
    }
}
```

Tags: concurrency, shutdown, gateway
